The paper focuses on techniques for finding vulnerabilities and generating test-cases for programs, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper specifically discusses fuzzing and symbolic execution, which are commonly used in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents an open-source framework, which could fall under the programming languages (cs.PL) category. The use of SMT solvers in the paper could also place it under the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper's title mentions "improving function coverage," which is a common concern in software engineering, further supporting the likelihood of cs.SE as the most likely category.
